<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph pageId="7" pageNumber="38">Status. Native Pontocaspian species (Black Sea Basin), Holocene invasive in Caspian Sea and Aral Sea.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="7" pageNumber="38">Type locality. French Mediterranean.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="7" pageNumber="38">
Distribution. NE Atlantic, Baltic Sea, Mediterranean, Black Sea Basin, Caspian Sea Basin, Aral Sea, isolated Saharan lakes (
<bibRefCitation author="Plaziat, J-C" journalOrPublisher="Journal of African Earth Sciences (and the Middle East)" pageId="81" pageNumber="112" pagination="383 - 389" title="Paleogeographic significance of the Cardium, Potamids and Foraminifera living in intra-continental salt lakes of North Africa (Sahara Quaternary, Egypt Present lakes)." url="https://doi.org/10.1016/0899-5362(91)90087-F" volume="12" year="1991">Plaziat 1991</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph pageId="7" pageNumber="38">
Taxonomic notes. DNA studies have shown a strong structuring between 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Atlantic–western">Atlantic-western</normalizedToken>
Mediterranean, Ionian, and Aegean-Pontocaspian populations of 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. glaucum" pageId="7" pageNumber="38" rank="species" species="glaucum">C. glaucum</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Nikula, R" journalOrPublisher="Marine Biology" pageId="80" pageNumber="111" pagination="339 - 350" title="Phylogeography of Cerastodermaglaucum (Bivalvia: Cardiidae) across Europe: a major break in the Eastern Mediterranean." url="https://doi.org/10.1007/s00227-003-1088-6" volume="143" year="2003">
Nikula and 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Väinölä">Vaeinoelae</normalizedToken>
2003
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Sromek, L" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Molluscan Studies" pageId="83" pageNumber="114" pagination="515 - 524" title="Strong genetic structuring of the cockle Cerastodermaglaucum across Europe: new insights from an intronic marker and multivariate analysis." url="https://doi.org/10.1093/mollus/eyw019" volume="82" year="2016">Sromek et al. 2016</bibRefCitation>
). According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Sromek, L" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Molluscan Studies" pageId="83" pageNumber="114" pagination="515 - 524" title="Strong genetic structuring of the cockle Cerastodermaglaucum across Europe: new insights from an intronic marker and multivariate analysis." url="https://doi.org/10.1093/mollus/eyw019" volume="82" year="2016">Sromek et al. (2016</bibRefCitation>
: 515), the &quot;strong genetic differentiation and the occurrence of private alleles may hint at the presence of cryptic species within 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. glaucum" pageId="7" pageNumber="38" rank="species" species="glaucum">C. glaucum</taxonomicName>
&quot;. For a discussion on the authority of 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. glaucum" pageId="7" pageNumber="38" rank="species" species="glaucum">C. glaucum</taxonomicName>
, see 
<bibRefCitation author="Vinarski, MV" journalOrPublisher="Severtsov Institute of Ecology and Evolution of RAS, Moscow" pageId="86" pageNumber="117" title="Analytical catalogue of fresh and brackish water molluscs of Russia and adjacent countries. A. N." year="2016">Vinarski and Kantor (2016</bibRefCitation>
: 69-70).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="7" pageNumber="38">
Remarks. The arrival of 
<taxonomicName class="Bivalvia" family="Cardiidae" genus="Cerastoderma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cerastoderma glaucum" order="Cardiida" pageId="7" pageNumber="38" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="glaucum">Cerastoderma glaucum</taxonomicName>
in the Caspian Sea circa 8000 years ago has been linked to human settlement expansion through the Manych corridor (
<bibRefCitation author="Fedorov, PV" journalOrPublisher="Trudy Geologicheskogo Instituta Akademii Nauk SSSR" pageId="74" pageNumber="105" pagination="1 - 298" title="Stratigrafiya chetvertichnykh otlozheniy i istoriya razvitiya Kaspiyskogo Morya." url="http://www.ginras.ru/library/pdf/10_1957_fedorov_quaternary_caspian.pdf" volume="10" year="1957">Fedorov 1957</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Yanina, TA" journalOrPublisher="Majenta, Smolensk-Moskva" pageId="87" pageNumber="118" url="http://www.geogr.msu.ru/structure/labs/notl/personal/Abstracts/Yanina_avtoreferat.2009.pdf" year="2009">Yanina 2009</bibRefCitation>
). It would be among the earliest human-mediated dispersal events for invertebrate species known to date.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
